    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_825DA450-1E46-0135-B5FB-22000B5A851D" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can add a grading scheme to customize assignment grading. You can use grading schemes created by your institution, grading schemes created  or you can <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-add-a-grading-scheme-in-a-course/ta-p/1054" target="_blank">create a new grading scheme.</a></p>
<p><strong>Notes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>When an assignment is part of selected content in a course export, the grading scheme for the assignment will also be imported. </li>
<li>Using an account-level grading scheme built by your institution links the scheme into your course—it does not import as a new scheme on the course level. </li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_assignments" data-step-uuid="C438ADB4-CA45-498F-BB11-A6E8E6390D84">
    <h2 id="open_assignments" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Open Assignments</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/002/743/351/original/eda740e4-883a-4fd7-99a8-30747f660b0c.png" srcset="" alt="Open Assignments" height="271" width="169">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_825DDC90-1E46-0135-B5FD-22000B5A851D" class="text-block-content">
    <p>In Course Navigation, click the <strong>Assignments</strong> link.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_assignment" data-step-uuid="FDF41206-A0A0-40C3-95B8-2D53F0F8F54E">
